<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idca473bfa-3a70-11f1-bde1-a5140e158598" identifier="/us/usc/t43/s1599"><num value="1599">§ 1599.</num><heading> Definitions</heading>
<chapeau style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">As used in this subchapter—</chapeau><subsection style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="idca473bfb-3a70-11f1-bde1-a5140e158598" identifier="/us/usc/t43/s1599/a"><num value="a">(a)</num><content> all terms that are defined in the Colorado River Compact shall have the meanings therein defined;</content>
</subsection>
<subsection style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="idca473bfc-3a70-11f1-bde1-a5140e158598" identifier="/us/usc/t43/s1599/b"><num value="b">(b)</num><content> “Colorado River Basin States” means the States of Arizona, California, Colorado, Nevada, New Mexico, Utah, and Wyoming.</content>
</subsection>
<sourceCredit id="idca473bfd-3a70-11f1-bde1-a5140e158598">(<ref href="/us/pl/93/320/tII/s209">Pub. L. 93–320, title II, § 209</ref>, <date date="1974-06-24">June 24, 1974</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/88/275">88 Stat. 275</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
</section>
